---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Oven Temperature Guide: Celsius to Fahrenheit for Baking" description="Complete oven temperature conversion chart from Celsius to Fahrenheit and Gas Marks. Never ruin a recipe because of wrong temperature settings again." keywords="oven temperature, celsius to fahrenheit oven, baking temperature, gas mark conversion, oven conversion chart, cooking temperature, recipe temperature">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Temperature</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Oven Temperature Guide: Celsius to Fahrenheit for Baking</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 19, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>You have found a beautiful recipe online, but the oven temperature is in Celsius and yours displays Fahrenheit (or the other way around). This is one of the most common conversion problems in the kitchen. Here is your complete reference.</p>

      <h2>Oven Temperature Chart</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Very low:</strong> 120°C = 250°F (Gas Mark 1/2)</li>
        <li><strong>Low:</strong> 150°C = 300°F (Gas Mark 2)</li>
        <li><strong>Moderate:</strong> 160°C = 325°F (Gas Mark 3)</li>
        <li><strong>Moderate:</strong> 180°C = 350°F (Gas Mark 4)</li>
        <li><strong>Moderately hot:</strong> 190°C = 375°F (Gas Mark 5)</li>
        <li><strong>Hot:</strong> 200°C = 400°F (Gas Mark 6)</li>
        <li><strong>Hot:</strong> 220°C = 425°F (Gas Mark 7)</li>
        <li><strong>Very hot:</strong> 230°C = 450°F (Gas Mark 8)</li>
        <li><strong>Extremely hot:</strong> 250°C = 480°F (Gas Mark 9)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Formula</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">°F = (°C × 9/5) + 32</p>
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400 mt-1">°C = (°F - 32) × 5/9</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Common Baking Temperatures</h2>
      <p>Most recipes fall into a few standard temperatures:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> 180°C / 350°F — the most common baking temperature</li>
        <li><strong>Cakes:</strong> 160-180°C / 325-350°F</li>
        <li><strong>Bread:</strong> 200-230°C / 400-450°F</li>
        <li><strong>Pizza:</strong> 220-250°C / 425-480°F (as hot as home ovens go)</li>
        <li><strong>Meringues:</strong> 100-120°C / 210-250°F (very low and slow)</li>
        <li><strong>Roast chicken:</strong> 200°C / 400°F</li>
        <li><strong>Slow roast:</strong> 150°C / 300°F</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Fan Oven Adjustment</h2>
      <p>If your recipe gives a temperature for a conventional oven but you have a fan (convection) oven, reduce the temperature by 20°C (or about 25°F). Fan ovens circulate hot air, cooking food faster and more evenly.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Recipe says 200°C conventional = use 180°C fan</li>
        <li>Recipe says 180°C conventional = use 160°C fan</li>
        <li>Recipe says 400°F conventional = use 375°F fan</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tips for Accurate Oven Temperatures</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Get an oven thermometer</strong> — most ovens are off by 10-25°F from what the dial says</li>
        <li><strong>Always preheat</strong> — give your oven at least 10-15 minutes to reach temperature</li>
        <li><strong>Avoid opening the door</strong> — each opening drops temperature by 25°F (14°C)</li>
        <li><strong>Know your hot spots</strong> — rotate trays halfway through baking for even results</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/temperature" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Temperature Converter →</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
